defs.docs: `BitVec` – `Vec<bool>` in overdrive.

defs.name: Bits
defs.value:
Bits: Sealed + Binary + BitAnd<Self, Output = Self> + BitAndAssign<Self> +
BitOrAssign<Self> + Copy + Debug + Default + Display + Eq + From<u8> +
LowerHex + Not<Output = Self> + Shl<u8, Output = Self> + ShlAssign<u8> +
Shr<u8, Output = Self> + ShrAssign<u8> + Sized + UpperHex
defs.docs: A trait for types that can be used as direct storage of bits.

defs.name: WIDTH
defs.docs: The width in bits of this type.

defs.name: BITS
defs.docs:
The number of bits required to *index* the type. This is always
 log<sub>2</sub> of the type width.

defs.name: MASK
defs.docs:
The bitmask to turn an arbitrary usize into the bit index. Bit indices
 are always stored in the lowest bits of an index value.

defs.name: MAX_ELT
defs.docs: The maximum number of this type that can be held in a `BitVec`.

defs.name: set
defs.value: fn (&mut self, place: u8, value: bool) -> ()
defs.docs: Set a specific bit in an element to a given value.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Get a specific bit in an element.

defs.name: ones
defs.docs: Counts how many bits are set.

defs.name: zeros
defs.docs: Counts how many bits are unset.

defs.name: split
defs.docs: Splits a `usize` cursor into an (element, bit) tuple.

defs.name: join
defs.docs:
Joins a `usize` element cursor and `u8` bit cursor into a single
 `usize` cursor.

defs.name: TY
defs.docs:
Rust doesn’t (as far as I know) have a way to render a typename at
 runtime, so this constant holds the typename of the primitive for
 printing by Debug.

defs.name: Sealed
defs.docs: Marker trait to seal `Bits` against downstream implementation

defs.name: BigEndian
defs.docs:
Travels an element starting at the Most Significant Bit and ending at the
 Least Significant Bit.

defs.name: LittleEndian
defs.docs:
Travels an element starting at the Least Significant Bit and ending at the
 Most Significant Bit.

defs.name: Endian
defs.docs: A manipulator trait for Endianness.

defs.name: curr
defs.docs: Compute the bit index at a given count.

defs.name: next
defs.docs: Compute the semantic index that logically follows the given index.

defs.name: prev
defs.docs: Compute the semantic index that logically precedes the given index.

defs.name: jump
defs.docs:
Computes the bit index at a given semantic offset from the current
 cursor.

defs.name: BitSlice
defs.docs: A compact slice of bits, whose cursor and storage type can be customized.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Gets the bit value at the given position.

defs.name: set
defs.value: fn (&mut self, index: usize, value: bool) -> ()
defs.docs: Sets the bit value at the given position.

defs.name: all
defs.docs: Returns true if *all* bits in the slice are set (logical `∧`).

defs.name: any
defs.docs: Returns true if *any* bit in the slice is set (logical `∨`).

defs.name: not_all
defs.docs: Returns true if *any* bit in the slice is unset (logical `¬∧`).

defs.name: not_any
defs.docs: Returns true if *all* bits in the slice are unset (logical `¬∨`).

defs.name: some
defs.docs:
Returns true if some, but not all, bits are set and some, but not all,
 are unset.

defs.name: count_ones
defs.docs: Counts how many bits are set high.

defs.name: count_zeros
defs.docs: Counts how many bits are set low.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of bits contained in the `BitSlice`.

defs.name: elts
defs.docs: Counts how many *whole* storage elements are in the `BitSlice`.

defs.name: bits
defs.docs: Counts how many bits are in the trailing partial storage element.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the slice contains no bits.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Provides read-only iteration across the collection.

defs.name: for_each
defs.docs: Provides mutable traversal of the collection.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: Permits iteration over a `BitSlice`

defs.name: BitVec
defs.docs: A compact `Vec` of bits, whose cursor and storage type can be customized.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Constructs a new, empty, `BitVec<E, T>`.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs: Constructs a new, empty `BitVec<T>` with the specified capacity.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Returns the number of bits the vector can hold without reallocating.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Appends a bit to the collection.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs: Removes the last bit from the collection.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Empties out the `BitVec`, resetting it to length zero.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs: Reserves capacity for additional bits.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity to fit at least as much as is needed, but with as
 little or as much excess as the allocator chooses.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs: Shrinks the `BitVec` to the given size, dropping all excess storage.

defs.name: into_boxed_slice
defs.docs:
Converts the `BitVec` into a boxed slice of storage elements. This drops
 all `BitVec` management semantics, including partial fill status of the
 trailing element or endianness, and gives ownership the raw storage.

defs.name: set_store
defs.docs: Sets the backing storage to the provided element.

defs.name: set_len
defs.docs: Sets the length directly.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: Iterates over an owned `BitVec`.
